Implemented the Web API and SQL Server backend anchored to LCP-UML-9.

- Added EF Core SQL Server tooling in `LCP-UML-9/src/IdentityPublicServices/IdentityPublicServices.csproj` and wired up `AddDbContext` in `Program.cs` with a default connection string in `appsettings.json`.
- Modeled the validated UML domain in 3NF with rowversion concurrency tokens across identity, service, and agency aggregates (`Domain/Entities/*.cs`), including TPH inheritance for `Person` and `Agency`.
- Built `Infrastructure/Data/AppDbContext.cs` with precise relationships, rowversion mappings, and one-to-one/one-to-many constraints aligned to the PlantUML composition/aggregation lines.
- Implemented critical controllers using `IsolationLevel.Serializable` and optimistic concurrency: `IdentityRegistriesController`, `PassportServicesController`, and `AuditTrailsController`; added ghost-write–safe updates for `DriversLicensesController` and `VotingRegistriesController` (rowversion must be supplied on updates).

Next steps (run in `LCP-UML-9/src/IdentityPublicServices`):
1) `dotnet restore` (NuGet was unreachable earlier) then `dotnet ef migrations add InitialSchema && dotnet ef database update`.
2) Adjust `"DefaultConnection"` in `appsettings*.json` to your SQL Server.
3) When issuing PUTs to rowversion-protected endpoints, include the `RowVersion` byte[] from the last read to avoid 409 conflicts.
